Social grant beneficiaries will be receiving an increase from Tuesday. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Social grant beneficiaries will be receiving an increase from Tuesday. READ: Sassa suspends 500 suspicious grants Both child support grants and the grant-in-aid will go up to R430 per child. The increases were announced in Finance Minister Tito Mboweni's budget speech earlier this year. READ: Over 99000 grant beneficiaries yet to collect new cards Paseka Letsatsi, the South African Social Security Agency spokesperson said the increase is an add-on to the initial increase that took effect earlier this year.